RANDFONTEIN &#8211; South Africa mines minister Mosebenzi Zwane said on Thursday he aimed to finish revisions to an industry charter in the first quarter of 2016 or the next quarter &#8220;at the latest&#8221;.Zwane was responding to questions at a briefing on the 2016 mine safety statistics. Launched in 2002 to redress racial imbalances that still define the post-apartheid economy, the charter was revised in 2010 and the government is again redrawing targets, which include requirements for black ownership.